Package: azul
Type: Package
Title: Thesis-Style Interpretation of Statistical Models and Tables (MJMS/DrPH)
Version: 0.1.0
Authors@R: person("AZul", email = "azulmachang@gmail.com", role = c("aut", "cre"))
Description: Turns fitted models, hypothesis tests, and result tables into
    ready-to-paste, manuscript-style interpretation paragraphs following the
    Malaysian Journal of Medical Sciences (MJMS) reporting style (Arifin et al.
    2016) and SAMPL guidelines used in USM MPH/DrPH epidemiology work. A single
    generic, interpret(), dispatches on the class of the object: linear,
    logistic, Poisson/negative-binomial, ordinal, multinomial and conditional
    logistic regression; GEE and zero-inflated count models; Cox proportional
    hazards, Kaplan-Meier and parametric survival; linear mixed models;
    MANOVA/MANCOVA; structural equation and factor models; and common htest
    objects. Output is third-person, past-tense academic prose that always
    reports 95 percent confidence intervals, states the reference category,
    names the test, and reminds the user of the key assumptions to check.
    Result tables or 'gtsummary' objects are handled by interpret_table().
